# Expo & React Native Standards

## Documentation First

Before writing Expo-specific code, consult the versioned docs:
https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v57.0.0/

Do not rely on outdated patterns from earlier SDK versions.

## Stack (save-app)

- Expo SDK 57, Expo Router 57, React 19, React Native 0.86
- React Compiler enabled (`experiments.reactCompiler`) — avoid manual `memo`/`useMemo`/`useCallback` unless profiling proves they are needed
- Typed routes enabled (`experiments.typedRoutes`) — use typed `href` and `router` APIs
- Path alias: `@/` → `src/`

## Expo Router

- Screens live in `src/app/` following file-based routing.
- Use `_layout.tsx` for nested layouts and shared providers.
- Prefer `expo-router` navigation (`Link`, `router.push`, `Stack`, `Tabs`) over legacy React Navigation patterns.
- Handle loading, error, and empty states on every data-driven screen.

## Platform Awareness

- **Primary targets: iOS and Android.** Web is secondary; optimize layouts and interactions for native first.
- Use `Platform.select` or platform-specific files (`.ios.tsx`, `.android.tsx`, `.web.tsx`) when behavior diverges.
- Test Safe Area on notched devices via `react-native-safe-area-context`.
- Prefer Expo-compatible modules (`expo-image`, `expo-font`, etc.) over raw native dependencies.
- Do not add native modules or config plugins unless necessary and SDK-compatible.

## Mobile UX (iOS-first)

- Root app is wrapped in `AppProvider` (`GestureHandlerRootView` + `SafeAreaProvider` + `KeyboardProvider`).
- **Keyboard must never cover focused inputs.** Use `KeyboardScreen` or `KeyboardAwareScrollView` on any screen with `TextInput`.
- Use `AppTextInput` for all text fields — it sets `keyboardAppearance`, min touch height (44pt), and theme colors.
- Non-form screens: use `ScreenScrollView` with `contentInsetAdjustmentBehavior="automatic"` instead of nesting `SafeAreaView`.
- Android keyboard resize is configured via `softwareKeyboardLayoutMode: "resize"` in `app.json`.
- Dismiss keyboard on background tap via `KeyboardScreen`; use `keyboardDismissMode="interactive"` on iOS scroll views.
- Touch targets ≥ 44pt; use `MIN_TOUCH_TARGET` from `@/constants/mobile`.
- Prefer native tabs (`NativeTabs`) when building tab navigation; use Stack for simple flows.

## Styling

- Follow `StyleSheet.create` or NativeWind `className` patterns consistently.
- Reuse theme tokens from `@/constants/theme` and `useTheme()` — do not hardcode colors when tokens exist.
- Keep styles colocated with components; extract shared styles only when reused across files.

## Images & Assets

- Use `expo-image` for optimized image rendering.
- Provide appropriate `contentFit`, dimensions, and accessibility labels.

## Permissions & Native Config

- Any permission or `app.json` plugin change must be called out to the user with platform impact (iOS/Android/Web).
